## Phase 6: Fix Recommendation and Risk Assessment

Spawn two parallel assessment agents:

### Fix Confidence Assessment

Evaluate the proposed fix:

| Factor | Score (0-100) | Notes |
|--------|--------------|-------|
| Root cause clarity | | How well do we understand the actual cause? |
| Fix specificity | | Does the fix target exactly the root cause? |
| Test coverage | | Can we verify the fix with tests? |
| Similar patterns | | Are there other instances of the same bug? |
| **Overall fix confidence** | **weighted avg** | |

### Risk Assessment

Evaluate downstream risk of the proposed fix:

| Factor | Risk Level | Notes |
|--------|-----------|-------|
| Blast radius | Low/Med/High | How many callers/consumers are affected? |
| Behavioral change | Low/Med/High | Does this change observable behavior? |
| Data path impact | Low/Med/High | Does this affect data flow or persistence? |
| Concurrency impact | Low/Med/High | Does this affect threading or shared state? |
| Rollback difficulty | Low/Med/High | How hard to revert if something goes wrong? |
| **Overall risk** | **highest factor** | Conservative — take the worst score |

### Output

Complete the investigation file:

```markdown
## Fix Recommendation

### Proposed Fix
[Clear description of what to change and why]

### Fix Confidence: [X]%
[Summary of confidence factors]

### Risk Assessment: [Low/Medium/High]
[Summary of risk factors]

### Similar Patterns to Check
- [ ] [Other locations that may have the same bug]

### Recommended Approach
- [ ] [Step-by-step fix plan]
- [ ] [What tests to add]
- [ ] [What to verify after fixing]
```

