## Quick Reference

| Phase | What Happens | Output |
|-------|-------------|--------|
| 1. Intake | Parse bug report, create ticket if needed | Initial triage in investigation file |
| 2. Hypotheses | Form 3-10 ranked theories | Hypothesis table with logging plan |
| 3. Instrument | Create BugInvLogger + add file-based logging | Logger file + logging map + `*-runtime.log` path |
| 4. Validate | Read runtime log file, validate hypotheses | Confirmed root cause |
| 5. Forensics | Trace origin through git history | Introducing commit + classification |
| 6. Assess | Parallel confidence + risk scoring | Fix recommendation with scores |
| 7. Cleanup | Remove logger + calls, keep log file | Clean codebase + user summary + preserved logs |
